headlines.description: Arsenal returned to the top of the Premier League courtesy of a 1-0 win over London rivals Chelsea at Stamford Bridge on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Arsenal edge Chelsea, go top of Premier League

headlines.description: Manchester United suffered a damaging 3-1 defeat to Aston Villa at a lively Villa Park in Unai Emery's first match in charge.
headlines.shortLinkText: Villa down Man Utd to give Emery perfect debut

headlines.description: Newcastle United produced another ruthless display in a 4-1 win over struggling Southampton, with Miguel Almiron scoring again.
headlines.shortLinkText: Almiron scores again as Newcastle thrash Soton

events.name: Crystal Palace at West Ham United

headlines.description: — Michael Olise struck in the fourth minute of added time to secure a 2-1 win for Crystal Palace at West Ham on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Olise's late goal secures win for Palace at West Ham in EPL

headlines.description: — Mohamed Salah struck twice to fire Liverpool to a 2-1 win at Tottenham in the Premier League on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Salah double fires Liverpool to away win at Tottenham
